news.title: Existing home sales in U.S. climb for second straight month in July
news.para: Existing home sales increased 2.0% to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 5.99 million units last month from June's upwardly revised pace of 5.87 million units, the National Association of Realtors said on Monday.

news.title: Morbi ceramic industry faces additional burden of Rs 100 crore due to hike in gas price
news.para: ​Gujarat Gas, which supplies natural gas to ceramic manufacturing units in Morbi in Gujarat's Saurashtra region, on Monday announced a rise in industrial gas price under its agreement with effect from Tuesday.

news.title: India, ADB sign $500 million loan to expand Bengaluru metro rail network
news.para: "The new metro lines will further strengthen safe, affordable and green mobility in Bangaluru, having positive impact on enhancing quality of life, sustainable growth in urban habitat and livelihood opportunities," Mishra said.

news.title: Aptus Value Housing Finance India makes weak debut on exchanges
news.para: On BSE, the shares opened at Rs 329.95 which was 6.52 per cent below the issue price. Its opening price was also the lowest value the scrip had hit during the day. The scrip hit a high of Rs 354.6 and a low of Rs 329.95, during the trading session.

news.title: Nashik district land records can now be viewed & updated online
news.para: As a result, citizens can now search for property details online without having to visit the land records office. Moreover, they can also apply for updates to the records online.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: Last date to apply for town planning adalat extended to Sept 7
news.para: The applications for completion certificate, building number and building permit for residential constructions with dimensions below 120sqm, which are pending approval in corporation main office or zonal office, will be considered in the adalat.

news.title: Khola panchayat finds 'illegal construction' site abandoned
news.para: Nayak said that when they visited the spot, they could see no one at the construction site but the construction material and at least three stumps of felled coconut trees were lying around.

news.title: Multi-storeys built with thermocol could be quake-resistant buildings of future
news.para: Researchers at Indian Institute of Technology, Roorkee (IITR), have found that thermocol or Expanded Polystyrene (EPS) could resist earthquake forces on up to four-storey buildings.

news.title: Stop property transfer charge: Federation of Noida RWAs
news.para: While some residents maintain that there has been no appreciation in property prices in the past 5-6 years, others claim to be facing a financial crisis, especially due to job losses owing to Covid 19.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government to train 1,300 to ease land survey
news.para: The government has decided to depute senior moderators from the State Survey Training College at Samalkot in West Godavari district to the districts to launch the training session from August 26.

news.title: DDA receives 12,000 suggestions on draft Delhi master plan 2041
news.para: The draft MPD41, meant as a strategic and enabling framework for a sustainable and liveable Delhi in two decades, was made open to the public on June 9, originally for 45 days but later extended to August 23.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh CM directs officials to start 'option 3' houses from Oct 25
news.para: "Work of constructing houses for those who have chosen option three (the option to build houses by the government), should start from October 25," said Reddy.

news.title: Drone survey of 30,000 properties in three Bengaluru wards this week
news.para: The government, as part of a pilot, will be covering at least 30,000 properties spread across Pattabhiramnagar (number 168), Ganesh Mandir (number 165) and Shakambarinagar (number 179) wards.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Indirapuram Extension to be built on 12 acres only
news.para: The reason is the Ghaziabad Development Authority’s (GDA) inability to acquire land from local farmers at rates higher than the prevailing circle rate.

news.title: Centre aims to garner Rs 15,000 crore from monetisation of realty, hotel assets
news.para: ​In the 'urban real estate assets' category under the NMP, the government has identified monetisation of seven colonies under redevelopment as well as development of housing/commercial units on 240 acre land in Ghitorni in the national capital.
